f'(x)=1-\frac 32\cdot \frac 1{\sqrt{x+1}}
x=\frac 54
y=\left(\dfrac{x}{3}-\sqrt{x+1} \right)^2-2
P=x+y=\dfrac{x^2}{9}+2x-\dfrac{2x}{3}\sqrt{x+1}-1=f(x)
f'(x)=\dfrac{2x}{9}+2-\dfrac{3x+2}{3\sqrt{x+1}}
\dfrac{3x+2}{3\sqrt{x+1}}=\sqrt{x+1}-\dfrac{1}{3\sqrt{x+1}}<\sqrt{x+1} ,\implies f'(x)>\dfrac{2x}{9}+2-\sqrt{x+1}
(\dfrac{2x}{9}+2)^2-(x+1)=(\dfrac{2x}{9})^2-\dfrac{x}{9}+1=(\dfrac{2x}{9}-\dfrac{1}{2})^2+\dfrac{3}{4}>0 \implies f'(x) >0 
